<taxonomicName id="2B578494073720978CC621AD8565DE63" authority="Andre, 1896" authorityName="Bischoff" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudophotopsis binghami" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binghami">Pseudophotopsis binghami</taxonomicName>
Bischoff, 1920: 96, (♂ holotype), &quot;Perso-Baluch. Frontier&quot; (Iran).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DFEFD84CE8A535A5E1B350FBD2F59BEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">
<taxonomicName id="3F60A449B216D0BEFD91E67098774AF9" authority="Andre, 1896" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudophotopsis komarovii subsp. zarudnyi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="komarovii" subSpecies="zarudnyi">Pseudophotopsis komarovii subsp. zarudnyi</taxonomicName>
Skorikov, 1935: 292, (♂), &quot;Kerman, strana Sargad, Tshah-i-Zaman&quot; (Iran). Junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7A77AD7C96D19C185D259F21C3FC4D53" authority="Andre, 1896" authorityName="Bischoff" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudophotopsis binghami" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="binghami">Pseudophotopsis binghami</taxonomicName>
Bischoff, 1920 according to Lelej, 1985: 83.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7D5B535B2A4DBD675844F1D30CA9C9D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="77511B6FB0035535C85F1C033761418F" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="606EA245642BC1957FB119B136F4D1C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="75C075B5F131E5CB71838488740957EF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Male</emphasis>
. Body length 8-17 mm. Head and mesosoma (including legs) brown; metasoma black, 1st segment entirely and S2-S7 lighter; flagellomeres light brown; fore wing hyaline, with brown veins. Head with prolonged temples, weakly convergent behind eyes; distance between posterior ocellus and posterior head margin longer than longitudinal posterior ocellus diameter; POD 2.1-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="1E52C2131FDB9276D9D5E7DB401825D5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
OOD; F1 slightly shorter than F2 (0.9 
<normalizedToken id="C550C1EE9C1B4C7974A113D81988AAAC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
); basal lower mandibular tooth significantly bent downwards, distance between apex of lower tooth and upper mandibular ridge slightly longer than mandibular height at the base (see fig. 30 (8) in 
<bibRefCitation id="B43D7AA714E8B64AD536073707D34287" author="Lelej, AS" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B25" refString="Lelej, AS, 1985. The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries. Nauka, Leningrad" title="The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries." year="1985">Lelej 1985</bibRefCitation>
); S2 with well developed median basal tubercle; T2 basally and laterally with small dense foveae, becoming sparse on disc (several diameters distance apart); cuspis of volsella narrow at tip (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="86691A739E5D2FA54046E379804CEC58" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35D</figureCitation>
); parapenial lobe slightly oblique inward, with broadly rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2D7B074424F9161ACDE9E07AAA923BBD" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35C</figureCitation>
); genital ventral lobe rather cylindrical, extending directly posteriorly, with broadly rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E3DEBCB16EA506820E5BA09EC22990BC" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Male genitalia A, B Pseudophotopsis subaurea sp. nov., dorsal and ventral views, respectively C, D P. binghami Bischoff, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (modified from Lelej (1985))." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.82.65252.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/537916" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">35D</figureCitation>
). (
<bibRefCitation id="D1348EFDBEDDF0B5F60C9E9AAC4F50E0" author="Bischoff, H" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B7" refString="Bischoff, H, 1920. Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas [part]. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 86A (1/3): 1-480." title="Monographie der Mutilliden Afrikas [part]. Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte 86 A (1 / 3): 1 - 480." year="1920">Bischoff 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0A3430D1D4EA4AA70B3D3B56F696CA9C" author="Lelej, AS" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="361" refId="B25" refString="Lelej, AS, 1985. The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries. Nauka, Leningrad" title="The Velvet Ants (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae) of the USSR and Neighbouring Countries." year="1985">Lelej 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0115144933B32ACA9ECE57292873BD7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="FD58F1B169D0FF81F32CEA43977F8F81" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="361">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
